{"lemma":"شُرْفَةٍ","slug":"شُرْفَةٍ","root":"ش.ر.ف","root_slug":"ش-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22158","n22167","n22168"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"veranda"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"balcony, loge, theater box"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"battlement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gift on account of a new baby (given to the mother)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22158","headword_ar":"شرّفهُ","root":"$rf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oriyfN","text_ar":"تَشْرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered him high, elevated, exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in rank, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ennobled him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, KL, * PS: *) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he held him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"esteemed him, to be so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, PS.) ISd thinks that the verb may also mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He regarded with more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding, honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And Golius explains it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He decked with a royal garment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the authority of the KL; in my copy of which I find no other meaning assigned to it than the first mentioned above.] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~afa A@ll~`hu AlkaEobapa","text_ar":"شَرَّفَ ا@للّٰهُ الكَعْبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) inf. n. as above, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God rendered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God render, the Kaabeh an object of honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glorious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~arafu","text_ar":"الشَّرَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almajodu","text_ar":"المَجْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oriyfN","text_ar":"تَشْرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a subst. properly so called; and as such is expl. by itself in this art.] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put to it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uraf","text_ar":"شُرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urofapN","text_ar":"شُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]; (O, K;) namely, his house, (K,) or a [palace, or pavilion, or other building such as is called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.; inf. n. as above. (O.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafa AlHaAy^iTa","text_ar":"شَرَفَ الحَايِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~f AlmarobaA^a","text_ar":"شرّف المَرْبَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. in the K as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$rfhu","text_ar":"اشرفهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Arfhu","text_ar":"شارفهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$r~fhu","text_ar":"تشرّفهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~f Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"شرّف النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He almost severed the teats of the she-camel by binding them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tightly"},{"kind":"text","text":"] with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraAr","text_ar":"صِرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (IAar, O, TA:) this being done for the preservation of her [stoutness of] body, and her fatness, so that burdens may be put upon her in the coming year. (TA.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~f","text_ar":"شرّف"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~f","text_ar":"شرّف"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEunuqa","text_ar":"العُنُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also said by Reiske, as mentioned by Freytag in his Lexicon, to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel going along)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but his authority for this is not stated.]"}],"source_refs":["God","O","K","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n22167","headword_ar":"شُرْفَةٌ","root":"$rf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, first quarter. ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choice ones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning cattle]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urofap","text_ar":"شُرْفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a [palace, or pavilion, or other building such as is called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) [and of a mosque] is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1538},{"kind":"text","text":"well-known; (K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An acroterial ornament, forming a single member of a cresting of a wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the crown of a cornice, generally of a fanciful form, and pointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small, at the top:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urafN","text_ar":"شُرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA,) a pl. of mult., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urufaAtN","text_ar":"شُرُفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urafaAtN","text_ar":"شُرَفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urofaAtN","text_ar":"شُرْفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are pls. of pauc., or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$rfAt","text_ar":"شرفات"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urufaAtN","text_ar":"شُرُفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urufapN","text_ar":"شُرُفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs: EshShiháb says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urofaAt","text_ar":"شُرْفَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but what are thus termed are only"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are built on the top of a wall, distinct from one another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side by side, like merlons of a parapet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to a well-known form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urofap","text_ar":"شُرْفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is what is called by the [common] people ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aAfap","text_ar":"شُرَّافَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 824:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aAfap","text_ar":"شُرَّافَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a mosque is a word used by the lawyers, and is one of their mistakes, as IB has notified: so says MF: its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAriyfu","text_ar":"شَرَارِيفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urufaAt","text_ar":"شُرُفَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thus with two dammehs, K) of a horse are The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"croup,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the hips"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haunches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] thereof. (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22168","headword_ar":"شُرُفَةٌ","root":"$rf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}